    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required credibility levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level of 3 due to single loading rate and rod diameter evaluated; this gap is accepted given the standardized ASTM F1717 protocol and the medium model risk level. All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for the stated COU. Note: aleatory uncertainty arising from specimen geometric variability and material lot variation is discussed qualitatively in the validation report for the force-at-40mm result but has not been formally linked to a structured uncertainty quantification artifact for that result; this is acknowledged as a documentation gap that does not affect the overall acceptance decision given the conservative acceptance thresholds applied.",
